The minister of Information and Culture, Lai Mohammed, Tuesday, described those criticizing the bill as ill-informed citizens. He said that those condemning the bill have not read it or do not understand the bills provisions. Disclosing this at a press conference in Abuja, Lai Mohammed said: “Also, we cannot rule out deliberate mischief by some of those who have been portraying the Bill as a new source of conflict. “We are therefore using this opportunity to appeal to Nigerians to avail themselves of the provisions of the Bill to avoid being misled by those who have chosen to politicise it. “We also want to state that the Bill is for the good of the nation, and has no hidden agenda whatsoever. “Finally, when passed into law, the National Water Resources Bill 2020 will provide for the enhancement of the Nigeria Water Sector, in line with global best practices.” vanguardngr.com The minister of information, Lai Mohammed has denied any knowledge of the "social media" bill prior to its presentation in the 9th national assembly. The bill titled, “Protection From Internet Falsehood and Manipulations Bill, 2019” was sponsored by the Senator representing the Niger East, Mohammed Musa. Although the bill received… February 1, 2020 In "News" Soni Daniel - Abuja The Federal Government says there is nothing new about the National Water Resources Bill now generating controversy across the land. Information Minister, Lai Mohamed, made the declaration at a joint news conference with his Water Resources counterpart, Suleiman Hassan in Abuja. READ ALSO: Why FG is commercialising… September 22, 2020 In "News" Shina Abubakar - Osogbo The Senator representing Osun East Senatorial District, Francis Fadahunsi has alleged that the Minister of Information and Culture, Lai Mohammed is the mastermind behind the hate speech bill. Senator Fadahunsi said the hate speech bill was aimed at crippling quality journalism. Fadahunsi who was speaking with… December 29, 2019 In "Politics"